text: Burke is an unincorporated community in Grant County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Burke was established in 1907, and remained in operation until 1925. James M. Burke, an early postmaster, gave the community his name. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Grant County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Burke, Washington
